AmeriServ Postpones Offering
Donaldson, Lufkin  Jenrette Securities Corp., the lead
underwriter, had planned to issue more than 3.5 million
shares at $10 to $12 each. The company notified AmeriServ
that potential buyers believed IPO prices had gotten too
high, the company said.
   AmeriServ, which sells food service systems to
limited-menu chain resaurants, had planned to use the
proceeds to pay debt and to purchase warrants outstanding to
buy common stock of a subsidiary.